A variable stores data temporarily in memory so it can be reused throughout a shell script. 
It makes scripts more readable, reusable, and easier to maintain.

Declare a Variable
                 VARIABLE_NAME=value
                 NAME="Shahina"
                 AGE=24
                CITY="Palakkad"

 Access it using $:               
                 echo $NAME
                 
